# Observability programme delivery order

Follow `docs/opswatch-observability-programme.md` for all product work.

- Work in the documented phase order; do not skip ahead.
- Do not begin native Datadog or Dynatrace connectors until the generic
  synchronization and observability foundations are complete and verified.
- Placeholders, seeded data, schemas, interfaces, and navigation do not count
  as implemented capability.
- Require acceptance tests, runtime evidence, and local commits before
  progressing to the next phase.
- Never call unverified work complete.
- Do not push, deploy, or modify production without explicit approval.
- Position OpsWatch as an “Agentless application-health and
  incident-remediation platform with an advanced topology foundation.”
- Do not describe OpsWatch as Datadog-class or Dynatrace-class.
